-- File-type Icons (nvim-web-devicons)
-- Matches Antigravity IDE's bundled "Symbols" icon theme as closely as a
-- terminal font allows. Two layers:
--   1. Shape overrides ÔÇö the few types where Symbols' artwork diverges
--      from devicons' glyph choice (bare >_ shells, bare MÔåô markdown,
--      git diamond, gear, folders). Hand-matched nerd glyphs, exact SVG
--      colours. Filename keys are lowercase (devicons lowercases lookups);
--      names are unique so no highlight group is shared with defaults.
--   2. Colour alignment ÔÇö generated by sweeping the theme's JSON + SVGs
--      (Antigravity IDE.app/ÔÇª/theme-symbols/src/) against devicons'
--      tables: devicons keeps its glyph (same logo artwork), adopts the
--      theme's colour. One colour per highlight-name group, so entries
--      sharing a group can never conflict. 181 extensions +
--      129 filenames.
-- theme/colours.lua re-derives the DevIcon* highlights from these tables
-- after each colorscheme application (gruvbox would otherwise stomp them).
-- Folder glyphs live in plugins/nvim-tree.lua; folder slate colour in
-- theme/colours.lua (exempted from the greyscale sweep).

